name: Sewaddle
flavorText: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: Swadloon

abilities.name: Healing Leaves
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: Leavanny
flavorText: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

attack.name: Healing Wrapping
attack.text: Heal 100 damage from each of your Basic Pokémon.

attack.name: X-Scissor
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

attack.name: Absorb
attack.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Whimsicott ex

attack.name: Energy Gift
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Wondrous Cotton
attack.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. This attack does 50 damage for each Trainer card you find there.

name: Deerling
flavorText: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: Sawsbuck
flavorText: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

attack.name: Push Down
attack.text: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

name: Shelmet

abilities.name: Stimulated Evolution
abilities.text: If you have Karrablast in play, this Pokémon can evolve during your first turn or the turn you play it.

flavorText: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: Accelgor
flavorText: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

attack.name: Acid Spray
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Virizion
flavorText: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

attack.name: Giga Drain
attack.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Emerald Blade
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can’t use attacks.

name: Tepig
flavorText: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: Pignite
flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: Emboar

abilities.name: Inferno Fandango
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic {R} Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

attack.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Fire Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Pansear
flavorText: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

attack.name: Collect
attack.text: Draw a card.

name: Simisear
flavorText: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

name: Litwick
flavorText: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

attack.name: Brighten and Burn
attack.text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may discard that card.

name: Lampent
flavorText: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

attack.name: Fire Blast
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Chandelure
flavorText: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

attack.name: Incendiary Pillar
attack.text: If you have 10 or more Basic Fire Energy cards in your discard pile, this attack does 100 more damage.

attack.name: Burn It All Up
attack.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Heatmor
flavorText: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

attack.name: Licking Catch
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 in any combination of Fire Pokémon and Basic Fire Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Reshiram ex

attack.name: Blazing Burst
attack.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken. Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavorText: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

attack.name: Energized Shell
attack.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Samurott

abilities.name: Torrential Whirlpool
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

attack.name: Energized Slash
attack.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Basculin
flavorText: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

attack.name: Bared Fangs
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon has no damage counters on it before this attack does damage, this attack does nothing.

name: Ducklett
flavorText: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food–peat moss.

attack.name: Firefighting
attack.text: Discard a Fire Energy from your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Swanna
flavorText: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

attack.name: Air Slash
attack.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Vanillite
flavorText: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

attack.name: Ice Edge
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Vanillish
flavorText: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

attack.name: Ice Beam
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vanilluxe
flavorText: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

attack.name: Double Freeze
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads. If either of them is heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Keldeo ex

attack.name: Gale Thrust
attack.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

attack.name: Sonic Edge
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

attack.name: Electrobullet
attack.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

attack.name: Surprise Attack
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

attack.name: Discharge
attack.text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

attack.name: Muddy Bolt
attack.text: If this Pokémon has any Fighting Energy attached, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Woobat
flavorText: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

attack.name: Happy Return
attack.text: Put 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

attack.name: Reflect
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 40 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Telekinesis
attack.text: This attack does 70 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Yamask
flavorText: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

attack.name: Focused Wish
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Cofagrigus
flavorText: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

attack.name: Extended Damagriiigus
attack.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon.

attack.name: Perplex
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Gothita
flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

attack.name: Fortunate Eye
attack.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent’s deck and put them back in any order.

name: Gothitelle

abilities.name: Distorted Future
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may have your opponent shuffle their hand into their deck and draw 3 cards.

flavorText: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

attack.name: Synchro Shot
attack.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Frillish
flavorText: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

attack.name: Oceanic Gloom
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, they can’t play any Item cards from their hand.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Jellicent ex

abilities.name: Oceanic Curse
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can’t play any Item cards or Pokémon Tool cards from their hand.

attack.name: Power Press
attack.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Energy attached (in addition to this attack’s cost), this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Roggenrola
flavorText: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

attack.name: Harden
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks if that damage is 40 or less.

name: Boldore
flavorText: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

attack.name: Smack Down
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon has Fighting Resistance, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Gigalith
flavorText: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

attack.name: Vengeful Cannon
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Fighting Pokémon.

name: Sawk
flavorText: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

attack.name: Rising Chop
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon isn’t a Pokémon ex, this attack does nothing. This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Archen
flavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

attack.name: Acrobatics
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Archeops

abilities.name: Ancient Wing
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may devolve 1 of your opponent’s evolved Pokémon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent’s hand.

flavorText: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

attack.name: Smash Uppercut
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Resistance.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

attack.name: Retaliate
attack.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent’s last turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

attack.name: Invite Evil
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Darkness Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Liepard
flavorText: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

attack.name: Knock Off
attack.text: Discard a random card from your opponent’s hand.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

attack.name: Ruffians Attack
attack.text: Flip a coin for each Darkness Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

attack.name: Gunk Shot
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

attack.name: Take Down
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

attack.name: Mind Jack
attack.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon.

attack.name: Foul Play
attack.text: Choose 1 of your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Vullaby
flavorText: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

name: Mandibuzz

abilities.name: Look for Prey
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may use this Ability. Your opponent reveals their hand, and you put a Basic Pokémon with 70 HP or less that you find there onto your opponent’s Bench.

flavorText: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

name: Deino
flavorText: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

attack.name: Body Slam
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

attack.name: Double Hit
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Hydreigon ex

abilities.name: Greedy Eater
abilities.text: If your opponent’s Basic Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack used by this Pokémon, take 1 more Prize card.

attack.name: Dark Bite
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

attack.name: Power Whip
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Durant
flavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

attack.name: Bite Together
attack.text: If Durant is on your Bench, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

attack.name: Shred
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Ambush
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Patrat
flavorText: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

attack.name: Procurement
attack.text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Watchog
flavorText: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

attack.name: Focus Energy
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon’s Hyper Fang attack’s base damage is 240.

attack.name: Hyper Fang
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lillipup
flavorText: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

attack.name: Play Rough
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Herdier
flavorText: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

attack.name: Roar
attack.text: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

name: Stoutland
flavorText: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

attack.name: Odor Sleuth
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. Put a number of cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile into your hand.

attack.name: Special Fang
attack.text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 100 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Bouffalant ex

abilities.name: Bouffer
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Gold Breaker
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Tornadus
flavorText: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

attack.name: Wrapped in Wind
attack.text: Attach a Basic Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon.

attack.name: Hurricane
attack.text: Move a Basic Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Antique Plume Fossil

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text:
Play this card as if it were a 60-HP Basic Colorless Pokémon. This card can’t be affected by any Special Conditions and can’t retreat. At any time during your turn, you may discard this card from play. Ability ⇢ Plume Protection
As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent’s Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon Tool rule: You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.
name: Brave Bangle

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: If the Pokémon this card is attached to doesn’t have a Rule Box, the attacks it uses do 30 more damage to your opponent’s Active Pokémon ex (before applying Weakness and Resistance). (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Cheren

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Draw 3 cards.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Energy Retrieval

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Put up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Harlequin

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Each player shuffles their hand into their deck. Then, flip a coin. If heads, you draw 5 cards, and your opponent draws 3 cards. If tails, you draw 3 cards, and your opponent draws 5 cards.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Hilda

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Search your deck for an Evolution Pokémon and an Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

rules: · Item rule: You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
name: Tool Scrapper

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Choose up to 2 Pokémon Tools attached to Pokémon (yours or your opponent’s) and discard them.

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: If this card is attached to 1 of your Pokémon, discard it at the end of your turn. As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy. If this card is attached to an Evolution Pokémon, it provides ColorlessColorlessColorless Energy instead.

attack.name: Double Freeze
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads. If either of them is heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

attack.name: Electrobullet
attack.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

attack.name: Surprise Attack
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

attack.name: Discharge
attack.text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

attack.name: Muddy Bolt
attack.text: If this Pokémon has any Fighting Energy attached, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Woobat
flavorText: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

attack.name: Happy Return
attack.text: Put 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

attack.name: Reflect
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, this Pokémon takes 40 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Telekinesis
attack.text: This attack does 70 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon. This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Yamask
flavorText: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

attack.name: Focused Wish
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Cofagrigus
flavorText: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

attack.name: Extended Damagriiigus
attack.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokémon to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon.

attack.name: Perplex
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Gothita
flavorText: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: Gothorita
flavorText: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

attack.name: Fortunate Eye
attack.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent’s deck and put them back in any order.

name: Frillish
flavorText: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

attack.name: Oceanic Gloom
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, they can’t play any Item cards from their hand.

name: Roggenrola
flavorText: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

attack.name: Harden
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks if that damage is 40 or less.

name: Boldore
flavorText: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

attack.name: Smack Down
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon has Fighting Resistance, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Gigalith
flavorText: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

attack.name: Vengeful Cannon
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Fighting Pokémon.

name: Sawk
flavorText: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

attack.name: Rising Chop
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon isn’t a Pokémon ex, this attack does nothing. This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Archen
flavorText: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

attack.name: Acrobatics
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Archeops

abilities.name: Ancient Wing
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may devolve 1 of your opponent’s evolved Pokémon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent’s hand.

flavorText: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: Mienfoo
flavorText: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: Mienshao
flavorText: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

attack.name: Smash Uppercut
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by Resistance.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

attack.name: Retaliate
attack.text: If any of your Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent’s last turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Purrloin
flavorText: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

attack.name: Invite Evil
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Darkness Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Liepard
flavorText: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

attack.name: Knock Off
attack.text: Discard a random card from your opponent’s hand.

name: Scraggy
flavorText: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: Scrafty
flavorText: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

attack.name: Ruffians Attack
attack.text: Flip a coin for each Darkness Pokémon you have in play. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

attack.name: Gunk Shot
attack.text: Your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

attack.name: Take Down
attack.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Zoroark
flavorText: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

attack.name: Mind Jack
attack.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your opponent’s Benched Pokémon.

attack.name: Foul Play
attack.text: Choose 1 of your opponent’s Active Pokémon’s attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Vullaby
flavorText: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

name: Mandibuzz

abilities.name: Look for Prey
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may use this Ability. Your opponent reveals their hand, and you put a Basic Pokémon with 70 HP or less that you find there onto your opponent’s Bench.

flavorText: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

name: Deino
flavorText: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

attack.name: Body Slam
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent’s Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Zweilous
flavorText: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

attack.name: Double Hit
attack.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

attack.name: Power Whip
attack.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent’s Pokémon for each Energy attached to this Pokémon. (Don’t apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Durant
flavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

attack.name: Bite Together
attack.text: If Durant is on your Bench, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Druddigon
flavorText: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

attack.name: Shred
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

attack.name: Ambush
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Patrat
flavorText: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

attack.name: Procurement
attack.text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Watchog
flavorText: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

attack.name: Focus Energy
attack.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon’s Hyper Fang attack’s base damage is 240.

attack.name: Hyper Fang
attack.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lillipup
flavorText: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

attack.name: Play Rough
attack.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Herdier
flavorText: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

attack.name: Roar
attack.text: Switch out your opponent’s Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

name: Stoutland
flavorText: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

attack.name: Odor Sleuth
attack.text: Flip 3 coins. Put a number of cards up to the number of heads from your discard pile into your hand.

attack.name: Special Fang
attack.text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 100 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Whimsicott ex

attack.name: Energy Gift
attack.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

attack.name: Wondrous Cotton
attack.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. This attack does 50 damage for each Trainer card you find there.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Reshiram ex

attack.name: Blazing Burst
attack.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken. Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Keldeo ex

attack.name: Gale Thrust
attack.text: If this Pokémon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

attack.name: Sonic Edge
attack.text: This attack’s damage isn’t affected by any effects on your opponent’s Active Pokémon.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Jellicent ex

abilities.name: Oceanic Curse
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can’t play any Item cards or Pokémon Tool cards from their hand.

attack.name: Power Press
attack.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Energy attached (in addition to this attack’s cost), this attack does 80 more damage.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Hydreigon ex

abilities.name: Greedy Eater
abilities.text: If your opponent’s Basic Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack used by this Pokémon, take 1 more Prize card.

attack.name: Dark Bite
attack.text: During your opponent’s next turn, the Defending Pokémon can’t retreat.

rules: · Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.
name: Bouffalant ex

abilities.name: Bouffer
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attack.name: Gold Breaker
attack.text: If your opponent’s Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 100 more damage.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Harlequin

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Each player shuffles their hand into their deck. Then, flip a coin. If heads, you draw 5 cards, and your opponent draws 3 cards. If tails, you draw 3 cards, and your opponent draws 5 cards.

rules: · Supporter rule: You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
name: Hilda

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Search your deck for an Evolution Pokémon and an Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Hilda

abilities.name: Effect
abilities.text: Search your deck for an Evolution Pokémon and an Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Victini
flavorText: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

attack.name: V-Force
attack.text: If you have 4 or fewer Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.
